The Magnificent Universe of Birds

Birds, with over 10,000 species globally, are diverse, colorful, and known for their ability to fly. They are characterized by their feathers, used for flight, insulation, and courtship displays. Birds range from tiny hummingbirds to the large albatross with an impressive wingspan.

